Generate an Ordinal Sequence from a Number

Source: R/ordinal_seq.R
ordinal_seq.Rd

This function generates an ordinal sequence of an arbitrary length. For example, if the length is 3, the function will return the vector c("1st", "2nd", "3rd").

Usage

ordinal_seq(length)

Arguments

length

The length of the ordinal sequence to generate. It should be a numeric value of length 1.

Value

A vector of ordinal strings.

Examples

ordinal_seq(11)
#>  [1] "1st"  "2nd"  "3rd"  "4th"  "5th"  "6th"  "7th"  "8th"  "9th"  "10th"
#> [11] "11th"
